rm - rm stands for remove. It is used to remove a file.
Syntax - rm <file_name>

Following are the commands related to rm command which are as follows :-

1) To remove all the files having same extension - 
   Syntax - rm *<file_extension>
   
2) To delete a directory recursively - 
   Syntax - rm -r <directory_name>
   
3) To remove a file interactively - 
    Syntax - rm -i <file_name>
    
4) To remove a directory interactively - 
    Syntax - rm -ri <directory_name>
    
5) To remove a file forcefully -
   Syntax - rm -f <file_name>
   
6) To remove a directory forcefully -
   Syntax - rm -rf <file_name>
